k, such as AGN from\nintermediate mass black holes in lower mass galaxies, the baryonic fraction at\nthe virial radius can have a lower value (fb~0.12) at low redshift. Hence\nphysical mechanisms able to drive the gas out of the virial radius at high\nredshifts will have a stronger impact on the deficit of baryons in the mass\nbudget of Milky Way type-galaxies at present times than those that expel the\ngas in the longer, late phases of galaxy formation.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 21 May 2012 19:10:06 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 11 Sep 2012 06:25:36 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-05"}
